## R Task

Please follow the directions listed below

1.  Download the task files

<center>
<a onclick="fetch(&#39;data:application/zip;base64,&#39;).then(res =&gt; res.blob()).then(blob =&gt; {&#10;      const downloadURL = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);&#10;      const a = document.createElement(&#39;a&#39;);&#10;      document.body.appendChild(a);&#10;      a.href = downloadURL;&#10;      a.download = &#39;Introduction to the Tidyverse Task.zip&#39;; a.click();&#10;      window.URL.revokeObjectURL(downloadURL);&#10;      document.body.removeChild(a);&#10;    });">
<button class="btn btn-primary hvr-sweep-to-left"><i class="fa fa-save"></i> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style='color:#ffffff'>Download</span></button>
</a>
</center>

<br>

2.  [Unzip](/resources/unzipping) them on your computer

3.  Open the file `Data Wrangling Install.R` and run the syntax to install the packages you will need for this task

4.  Open the file `Data Wrangling walkthrough.Rmd` in RStudio

5.  Click on Run Document, and then go through the walkthrough preferably in a larger window. To see how to do this, open the file `Introduction to the Tidyverse loading.gif` from Week 2 in the web browser of your choice or by another method to view the animated gif

6.  After finishing the walkthrough, open the mostly empty Rmarkdown file `Data Wrangling Report.Rmd`, read through the body, and please make changes as directed to recieve credit.

7.  Save the resulting PDF file by adding your first initial and last name to the beginning of the filename. For example, my submission would be `aroy Data Wrangling walkthrough.pdf`

8.  Submit the script to [eCampus](https://ecampus.wvu.edu) in the Submission Portal
